  </article>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-surface-dim" aria-labelledby="faq-heading">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 id="faq-heading" class="font-display text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-800 text-ink tracking-wide uppercase mb-10">
        Frequently Asked <span class="text-accent">Questions</span>
      </h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8" open>
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            What is a conveyor pusher?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>A conveyor pusher pushes product off the side of a conveyor using a pneumatic cylinder or servo actuator. Pushers fire when a sensor detects product in position and a PLC triggers the push. Used for lane diverting, <a href="/conveyor-functions/reject-systems/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">reject systems</a>, and product routing.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            What is a blade diverter?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>A blade diverter uses a pivoting arm that swings into the product path at a 30 or 45 degree angle, deflecting product onto a spur conveyor. Blades handle cases, totes, and cartons at speeds up to 300+ FPM. Gentler than pushers because they redirect product momentum rather than applying lateral force.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            Pusher vs. diverter , what is the difference?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>A pusher applies lateral force perpendicular to the belt , fast but impactful. A diverter redirects product at an angle using existing forward momentum , gentler but requires more conveyor length. Use pushers for lightweight items and rejects. Use diverters for heavy products and gentle routing to multiple spur lines.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            How fast can pushers and diverters operate?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Pneumatic pushers: 50-200ms. Servo pushers: 30-100ms. Blade diverters: 100-500ms. ARB and sliding shoe sorters operate continuously with no cycle time limitation. The mechanism must complete its cycle before the next product arrives , at 200 FPM with 12-inch spacing, each product arrives every 300ms.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
